.SH NAME
ice_vsi_wait_one_rx_ring \- wait for a VSI's Rx ring to be stopped/started
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_vsi_wait_one_rx_ring
.BI "(struct ice_vsi *vsi "  ","
.BI "bool ena "  ","
.BI "u16 rxq_idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vsi" 12
the VSI being configured
.IP "ena" 12
true/false to verify Rx ring has been enabled/disabled respectively
.IP "rxq_idx" 12
0-based Rx queue index for the VSI passed in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine will wait for the given Rx queue of the VSI to reach the
enabled or disabled state. Returns -ETIMEDOUT in case of failing to reach
the requested state after multiple retries; else will return 0 in case of
success.
